"They constitute, however, a less serious condition than the other diseases studied here. 115 Ankylostomiasis (hookworm) may be one of the main causes of anemia. Amebiasis and giardiasis cause diarrhea. Apart from the link between hookworm and anemia, intestinal parasites have not been proven to play a role in malnutrition. No attempt will be made in this section to define the respective importance of each intestinal parasite, but it should be recognized that the complications these parasites occasion, particularly in pre-school-age children, can become a public health problem."